<item>
            <title>[LU-2241] symlink bug in 2.3.0</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2241</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Symlinks with a destination path that has the exact length of 61 characters don&apos;t work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;$ ln -s 123456789012345678901234567890123456789012345678901234567890&lt;br/&gt;
$ ls -al&lt;br/&gt;
ls: cannot read symbolic link 123456789012345678901234567890123456789012345678901234567890: Protocol error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Symlinks with shorter or longer paths work fine. I assume an off-by-one error, since 60 characters seems to be the limit for storing the symlink inside of an inode.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre 2.2.0 did not have this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>RHEL6.3</environment>
